.Dd $Mdocdate$
.Dt KHTTP_FCGI_PARSE 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm khttp_fcgi_parse ,
.Nm khttp_fcgi_parsex
.Nd parse a FastCGI instance for kcgi
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libkcgi
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In stdint.h
.In kcgi.h
.Ft "enum kcgi_err"
.Fo khttp_fcgi_parse
.Fa "struct kfcgi *fcgi"
.Fa "struct kreq *req"
.Fa "const char *const *pages"
.Fa "size_t pagesz"
.Fa "size_t defpage"
.Fc
.Ft "enum kcgi_err"
.Fo khttp_fcgi_parsex
.Fa "struct kfcgi *fcgi"
.Fa "struct kreq *req"
.Fa "const struct kmimemap *suffixes"
.Fa "const char *const *pages"
.Fa "size_t pagesz"
.Fa "size_t defmime"
.Fa "size_t defpage"
.Fa "void *arg"
.Fc
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm khttp_fcgi_parse
and
.Nm khttp_fcgi_parsex
functions parse and validate a single FastCGI request.
They may be invoked as many times as necessary, but must follow a call
to
.Xr khttp_fcgi_init 3
and be followed by
.Xr khttp_fcgi_free 3 .
.Pp
The collective arguments and return values are defined in
.Xr khttp_parse 3 .
.Pp
The
.Fa req
object filled in by
.Nm khttp_fcgi_parse
or
.Nm khttp_fcgi_parsex
must be subsequently freed by
.Xr khttp_free .
.Sh RETURN VALUES
These are the same as in
.Xr khttp_parse 3 ,
except the
.Dv KCGI_HUP
return code indicates that no more requests will arrive and the
application should exit.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr kcgi 3 ,
.Xr khttp_fcgi_init 3 ,
.Xr khttp_free 3
.Sh AUTHORS
The
.Nm khttp_fcgi_parse
and
